It appears that Proposal Notes and Indulgences may have ceased to
exist with the adoption of Proposal 3533.  Rule 1579/1 made the Mintor
of a Currency the Mint if no other specification existed.  Rule 1579/2
makes no such specification.  Neither Proposal Notes nor Indulgences
have a specified Mintor anywhere in the Rules; prior to Pr.3533 they
were therefore minted by the Mint through R.1579/1's default clause.
I suspect that, as a result of this, neither Proposal Notes nor
Indulgences have Mintor, and therefore fail to meet R.1579/2's
requirement of having a Mintor.

Suppose, however, we argue that the Mint remains the Mintor of these
Currencies.  This is still a problem, as the Mint also ceased to
exist, and more importantly ceased to have Mint Authority, with the
adoption of Pr.3533.  And Rule 1579/2 requires that a Currency be
destroyed if its Mintor ceases to exist or ceases to have Mint
Authority.

Note that this does not prohibit the making of Proposals; it only
prohibits the making of Interested Proposals.  It also breaks the Blot
systems badly, but that's not critical to the operation of the Game.
Voting Tokens are unaffected; Rule 1696 specifically states that the
Mintor of VTs is the Bank.

Comments?

