Harlequin wrote:

>And do you have a suggestion on how to handle situations where the Bank has
>a negative balance of Indulgences?

It may not be necessary to have negative balances (and it looks like Scott will
use the Chancellor's powers to prevent it anyway).  Something along the lines:

"Whenever Blots are created, the Herald shall calculate the surplus of Blots
equal to the number of Blots minus the number of Indulgences.  If this surplus
is greater than one, the Herald shall require the Bank to create enough
Indulgences to reduce this surplus to one."

"Whenever Fugitive Blots are created, and after the original Blots have been
vacated, the Herald shall calculate the surplus of Indulgences equal to one
plus the number of Indulgences minus the number of Blots.  If this surplus is
greater than zero, the Herald shall require the Bank to destroy either the
total number of Indulgences held by the bank or a number of Indulgences equal
to this surplus, whichever is less."

How does this sound?

-- Crito


